---
source: crates/llvm2-test/tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_of(&[\"fuzz\"])"
---
WS3 — Run differential fuzzers: csmith, yarpgen, tmir-gen

Usage: llvm2-test fuzz [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --driver <DRIVER>
          Which driver to run

          Possible values:
          - csmith:  csmith random C program generator
          - yarpgen: YARPGen random C/C++ program generator
          - tmirgen: In-tree tMIR random IR generator
          - all:     Run all drivers for the requested duration
          
          [default: all]

  -f, --format <FORMAT>
          Output format (human, json, junit)

          Possible values:
          - human: Pretty table + narrative, targeted at humans
          - json:  Machine-readable JSON following the schemas in `evals/schema/`
          - junit: JUnit XML for CI consumers
          
          [default: human]

      --duration <DUR>
          Wall-clock duration (humantime, e.g. `10s`, `1h`, `24h`)
          
          [default: 10m]

  -o, --out <PATH>
          Write machine-readable result artifact here. Default:
          `evals/results/<cmd>/<iso-date>.json`

      --config <PATH>
          Config file (TOML). Default: `llvm2-test.toml` at repo root

      --seeds <N>
          Number of seeds to run (cap; earlier of duration or seeds wins)

      --optlevel <N>
          Optimization level used when compiling generated programs
          
          [default: 2]

      --timeout <SECS>
          Per-unit timeout in seconds. Subcommands may apply per-unit defaults when this is unset

      --parallel <N>
          Worker count (honors cargo-serialization lock). Default: auto

      --reduce
          Run creduce on every miscompile before filing

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress progress bars; errors still go to stderr

  -v, --verbose...
          Show debug-level events. Repeat for more: -vv, -vvv

      --no-cache
          Ignore proof / corpus caches

      --dry-run
          Print what would run without executing external tools

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
